      "writtenOn": "2020-08-06T05:41:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Copying here is weird for a slice seemingly owned by optimizer.\nBetter to do this copying *before* you create an optimizer{} struct.\n\nGiven how little code there is here, consider (I don\u0027t insist) to just define vars \u0026 inner function instead of a dedicated struct (basically, same as my Python code):\n\nfunc OptimizeOrder(...) cls {\n  cls, _, _ ... :\u003d optimize(...)\n}\n\nfunc optimize(...) (everything you want to test against) {\n  // copy cls and initialize temporary maps \n\n  visit :\u003d func(...){\n  }\n\n  ...\n  return ordered, \u003cother stuff\u003e\n}",
      "range": {
